xworth, Suffolk, England":"Ixworth, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705183,"age":16,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":26,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":36,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Colekirke was born in 1070, in Ixworth, Suffolk, England, her father, Robert De Colekirke, was 25 and her mother, Gungreda Ferrers, was 25. She married Sir Gilbert le Blount 2nd Baron Ixworth in 1086, in Ixworth, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. She died in 1130, in her hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1070–1130":"1070–1130","1064–1166":"1064–1166","1089–Male":"1089–Surnud","1096–1169":"1096–1169","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","1045–1107":"1045–1107","1045–1086":"1045–1086","about 1096":"umbes 1096","1120":"1120","1054":"1054","1086":"1086","1130":"1130","1064":"1064","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","1107":"1107","1106":"1106","1169":"1169","1045":"1045","1089":"1089","1166":"1166","about 1089":"umbes 1089","Henford, Devon, England":"Henford, Devon, England","Ixworth, Suffolk, England":"Ixworth, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1070–1130":"1070–1130","1064–1166":"1064–1166","1089–Male":"1089–Kuollut","1096–1169":"1096–1169","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","1045–1107":"1045–1107","1045–1086":"1045–1086","about 1096":"noin 1096","1120":"1120","1054":"1054","1086":"1086","1130":"1130","1064":"1064","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","1107":"1107","1106":"1106","1169":"1169","1045":"1045","1089":"1089","1166":"1166","about 1089":"noin 1089","Henford, Devon, England":"Henford, Devon, England","Ixworth, Suffolk, England":"Ixworth, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1070–1130":"1070–1130","1064–1166":"1064–1166","1089–Male":"1089–Décédé","1096–1169":"1096–1169","1120–Female":"1120–Décédée","1045–1107":"1045–1107","1045–1086":"1045–1086","about 1096":"environ 1096","1120":"1120","1054":"1054","1086":"1086","1130":"1130","1064":"1064","1096":"1096","1070":"1070","1107":"1107","1106":"1106","1169":"1169","1045":"1045","1089":"1089","1166":"1166","about 1089":"environ 1089","Henford, Devon, England":"Henford, Devon, Angleterre","Ixworth, Suffolk, Englan